# Discard server — Caddy reverse proxy
#
# Replace "discard.example.com" with your actual domain before use.
#
# What this handles:
#   ✔  HTTP → HTTPS redirect (automatic)
#   ✔  TLS certificate via Let's Encrypt (automatic)
#   ✔  HTTP API (port 443 → 5000)
#   ✔  WebSocket upgrades (transparent — Caddy handles the Upgrade header)
#
# What this does NOT handle:
#   ✗  WebRTC / voice chat UDP ports (40000–40099)
#      These must be opened directly in the firewall — UDP cannot be proxied.
#      PUBLIC_ADDRESS in .env must still be your bare IPv4, not this domain.
#
# See the README for full setup instructions.

discard.example.com {
    reverse_proxy localhost:5000
}
